               #################### History of javascript  #######################

Birth of JavaScript (1995)-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
In 1995, the Internet and websites were becoming popular. At that time, websites were mostly static pages.
Example:
Welcome to my website
Contact Us
About Us
If a user clicked a button, nothing special happened on the page.
Netscape Communications wanted websites to become more interactive and dynamic.
Therefore, they hired Brendan Eich.
Brendan Eich created JavaScript in only 10 days.

Name Journey---------
The language was initially called Mocha and later changed to LiveScript.
In December 1995, LiveScript was renamed JavaScript,  
Note: JavaScript and Java are completely different languages. The name JavaScript was chosen mainly for marketing purposes because Java was very popular at that time.
Mocha---> LiveScript--->JavaScript


Problem (Browser Wars)---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1997–2005 ke beech:
Netscape Navigator aur Internet Explorer compete kar rahe the.
Dono browsers JavaScript ko alag tarike se implement karte the.
Different browsers implemented JavaScript differently.
Ek browser me chalne wala code dusre browser me error de deta tha.

Example:
Code works in Netscape
Doesn't work in Internet Explorer

Example:
Netscape Browser → Different behavior
Internet Explorer → Different behavior

Developers faced many compatibility issues.


Solution of War------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------




JavaScript was standardized.

An organization called ECMA International created a standard specification for JavaScript.
ECMA International ne JavaScript ke liye ek standard banaya:

This standard was named =====> ECMAScript

Difference--------------
JavaScript = Actual Programming Language
ECMAScript = Standard/Specification

Ab sab browsers ko isi standard ko follow karna tha.
1.  Better Browser Support--------
Browsers ne gradually ECMAScript standards ko adopt karna shuru kiya
Chrome
Firefox
Safari
Edge
sab ne same standards follow karne shuru kiye.

2. Cross-Browser Testing-------------
Developers alag-alag browsers me apne code ko test karne lage taaki har browser me website sahi chale.

Result-------
1.Better compatibility
2.Same JavaScript code multiple browsers me chalne laga
3.Web development easier ho gayi

in short-----------------
Browser Wars ki problem ko solve karne ke liye ECMAScript standard introduce kiya gaya. Is standard ne JavaScript ke rules define kiye, jise sab browsers ne follow kiya. Isse browser compatibility improve hui aur same code different browsers me sahi se chalne laga.


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ECMAScript 1 (ES1) – 1997

ECMAScript 1 was the first official standard version of JavaScript. Before ES1, different browsers implemented JavaScript differently. ES1 provided a common standard that all browsers could follow.

Main Features
1. Variables- Used to store data. Example---var name = "Reshma";

2. Functions - Used to write reusable code.
function greet() {
   console.log("Hello");
}

3. Loops - Used to repeat tasks.
for(var i=1; i<=5; i++) {
   console.log(i);
}

4. Conditions - Used for decision-making.
if(age >= 18) {
   console.log("Adult");
}
Benefit: ---- ES1 laid the foundation of JavaScript and made it a standardized language.


ECMAScript 2 (ES2) – 1998----------------------------------------------

ES2 was mainly a maintenance release.
What Changed->
Improved the language specification.
Fixed inconsistencies in the ES1 standard.
Improved browser compatibility.
New Feature - No major new programming features were introduced.
Benefit: Made JavaScript more stable and consistent across browsers.

ECMAScript 3 (ES3) – 1999--------------------------------------------------

ES3 was the first major update of JavaScript and greatly improved its capabilities.
1. Regular Expressions - Used for searching and matching text patterns.
let pattern = /abc/;
Example: console.log(pattern.test("abc123"));
Output: true
Benefit: Made text searching and validation easier.

2. Better String Handling -  with strings became easier.
let text = "Hello";
console.log(text.length);
Output: 5
Benefit: Easier text manipulation.

3. Try-Catch Error Handling - Used to handle errors safely.
try {
   console.log(x);
}
catch(error) {
   console.log("Error Found");
}
Output: Error Found
Benefit: Programs no longer crashed immediately when an error occurred.

4. Do-While Loop - tuns at least one time before checking the condition.
let i = 1;
do {
   console.log(i);
   i++;
} while(i <= 5);
Benefit: Useful when code must execute at least once.


ES1 (1997) → Introduced basic JavaScript features like Variables, Functions, Loops, and Conditions.

ES2 (1998) → Improved the standard and browser compatibility.

ES3 (1999) → Added powerful features like Regular Expressions, Better String Handling, Try-Catch Error Handling, and Do-While Loops, making JavaScript much more useful for real-world web development.
